You&#39;ll need to determine what encoding was used to create your file.
For example, if your file was written using utf-8 then you can use something like this:

    your_encoding = &#39;utf-8&#39;
    import codecs
    f = codecs.open(&#39;read.txt&#39;, encoding=your_encoding)
    for line in f:
        print repr(line)

Some other encodings you can try include &#39;cp1252&#39; which is common on Windows and maybe &#39;latin_1&#39;

[Reference](https://docs.python.org/2/howto/unicode.html#reading-and-writing-unicode-data)

